      <para id="para-00019">Looking at the truth table for the conditional statement, the only time the conditional is true, is when the hypothesis <emphasis effect="italic">p</emphasis> is also true. The only place this happens in the first row, where <emphasis effect="italic">q</emphasis> is also true, confirming that the law of detachment is a valid argument.</para>
